{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:52:47.860801+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "The write tool consistently returns a **403 (Resource not accessible by personal access token)** error, which means the token doesn't have write permissions to this repository. This cannot be resolved by retrying.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n### Issue #5: Update configuration reference\n\n**What was requested:** Expand the configuration reference with the documented output directory setting (`site_dir`), in `docs/configuration.md` and `mkdocs.yml`.\n\n### Proposed Changes\n\n**1. `docs/configuration.md`** — Add the `site_dir` row to the settings table:\n\n```markdown\n# Configuration\n\n| Setting | Description |\n| --- | --- |\n| `site_name` | Human-readable documentation site name. |\n| `site_dir` | Output directory where the generated site is written. Defaults to `site`. |\n```\n\n**2. `mkdocs.yml`** — Add `site_dir: site` explicitly:\n\n```yaml\nsite_name: Clean MkDocs Benchmark\nsite_description: Documentation benchmark repository\nsite_dir: site\nnav:\n  - Home: index.md\n  - Getting Started: getting-started.md\n  - Configuration: configuration.md\n  - API:\n      - Overview: api/overview.md\n      - Errors: api/errors.md\ntheme:\n  name: material\nmarkdown_extensions:\n  - admonition\n```\n\n### Validation\n\nThe `scripts/validate_repo.py` script checks for:\n- Required files: `README.md`, `SECURITY.md`, `mkdocs.yml`, `requirements.txt`, `docs/index.md` — all still present ✓\n- `mkdocs.yml` contains `site_name:` and `nav:` — both still present ✓\n\nThe proposed changes are safe and would continue to pass validation.\n\n### Limitation\n\nAll write operations (`create_or_update_file`, `push_files`) failed with **403 — Resource not accessible by personal access token**. The token lacks write permission to `rpnr-bench/T16_R01`. A repository admin would need to either grant the token write access or apply these changes manually.", "additional_kwargs": {"refu